A '''drag bit''' is a [[drill bit]] usually designed for use in soft formation, such as sand, clay, or some soft rock. Uses include drilling water wells, that consists of a [[drill pipe connector]] attached to blades on the end.  The cutting edge of the drag bit is often [[tungsten carbide]].  

A chevron bit is a type of drag bit designed for harder materials, commonly used for drilling [[oil well]]s.  Other types of drag bits include chevron, step, and scratcher.  Drag bits are generally used with Tungsten Carbide Inserts and are manufactured by Lone Star Bit (www.lonestarbit.com)

